    "finalText": "No relevant Teams messages from the past week surfaced in the evidence. That means I can’t pull any direct, up-to-date signal on people’s specific concerns or active worries from chat channels or DMs right now.\n\nThis is a gap: either the sync pipeline for Teams messages is lagging (which, given current system status, is likely) or conversations about major issues haven’t happened in Teams during that window. Right now, the broader context suggests critical source lags affecting Teams DM exports for key users (acannon@alleatogroup.com), which is a known pipeline bottleneck.\n\n**What this means:**  \nI can’t point to specific people, topics, or real-time pain points discussed in Teams for the last 7 days. Any summary would be guesswork — that’s not good enough.\n\n**What to do next:**  \n- If you need urgent signals, check recent meeting transcripts and email threads; those are less affected by sync lag.\n- If there’s a particular project or person you want a workaround for (e.g., RFI patterns, cost events, action items), specify — I can pull risk from other sources.\n\nIf you want, I can monitor for when Teams sync is restored and notify you as soon as the pipeline catches up. Let me know if you want to focus on a different signal surface (meeting, email, specific project)."
